The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, March 21: Qatar has agreed to supply India up to 4 million tonnes of additional LNG to meet its growing energy needs. The worlds largest LNG exporter will begin with one million tonne of supplies in 2011 and ramp it up to 4 million tonnes by 2014. These will be 15-20 year contracts, Qatars energy minister Abdullah al-Attiyah said.                            
	 New Delhi, March 21: Prime Minister Manmohan Singh will chair the Planning Commission meeting on Tuesday to review the economy. The meeting will also consider and approve the mid-term appraisal of the Eleventh Plan (2007-12), official sources said.                             
	 New Delhi, March 21: Drug major Cipla will replace its peer Sun Pharmaceuticals on the Bombay Stock Exchanges benchmark sensex from May 3. The index committee of the BSE, at a meeting held on March 19, decided to revise the composition of indices.                            
	 Frankfurt/ New Delhi, March 21: Siemens AG will axe 4,200 jobs at its IT business worldwide by 2011 as part of a reorientation plan. Siemens has a good presence in India, where it provides direct employment to over 17,000 people.                             
	 New Delhi, March 21: The finance ministry hopes to meet the Rs 3.87-lakh-crore target set for direct tax collections in the current fiscal. The ministry mopped up Rs 3.54 lakh crore from direct taxes till March 18.                                                                                                                          
